SIMPLE: confounded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Confounded
<hw>Con*found"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Confused;
perplexed; unclear in mind or intent; bewildered.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> at sea, befuddled, bemused, bewildered, confused,
mazed, mixed-up.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>A cloudy and <qex>confounded</qex> philosopher.</q>
<rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive; extreme; abominable.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a most <qex>confounded</qex> tory.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tongue of that <qex>confounded</qex> woman.</q> <rj><qau>Sir.
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confoundedly</ent>⟦br⟧
